cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper is primarily focused on language modeling using recurrent neural networks, which falls under the scope of this category. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel architecture for language modeling using hierarchical recurrent neural networks, which is a machine learning technique. 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper presents real-time character-level end-to-end speech recognition examples, which involves processing sound data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new approach to improve the performance of character-level language models, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.SD (Signal Processing): The paper involves processing speech data for end-to-end speech recognition, which falls under the scope of signal processing.
